338690201.name: Lusamine
338690201.text: Put 2 in any combination of Supporter and Stadium cards from your discard pile into your hand.

338690202.name: Mars
338690202.text: Draw 2 cards. If you do, discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

338690203.name: Pokémon Fan Club
338690203.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

338690204.name: Volkner
338690204.text: Search your deck for an Item card and a {L} Energy card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

abilities.name: Breath of the Leaves
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 50 damage from 1 of your Pokémon that has any Energy attached to it.

attacks.name: Grand Bloom GX
attacks.text: For each of your Benched Basic Pokémon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can’t use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Fast Raid
attacks.text: If you go first, you can use this attack on your first turn.

attacks.name: Cruel Spike
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Beauty GX
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage for each Prize card your opponent has taken. (You can’t use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

abilities.name: Freezing Gaze
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, your opponent’s Pokémon-GX and Pokémon-EX in play, in their hand, and in their discard pile have no Abilities, except for Freezing Gaze.

attacks.name: Frost Bullet
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Polar Spear GX
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage for each damage counter on your opponent’s Active Pokémon. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

abilities.name: Flashing Head
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon that have any Special Energy attached to them.

attacks.name: Lighting GX
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand. Add a card you find there to their Prize cards face down. (You can’t use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Rumbling Wires
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

abilities.name: Invasion
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Dark Flash
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

attacks.name: Moon's Eclipse GX
attacks.text: You can use this attack only if you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent. Prevent all effects of attacks, including damage, done to this Pokémon during your opponent's next turn. (You can’t use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Rocket Fall
attacks.text: This attack does 30 more damage for each {C} in your opponent's Active Pokémon's Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Blaster GX
attacks.text: Turn all of your Prize cards face up. (Those Prize cards remain face up for the rest of the game.) (You can’t use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Sun's Eclipse GX
attacks.text: You can use this attack only if you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent. (You can’t use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Meteor Tempest
attacks.text: Discard 3 Energy from this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Overclock
attacks.text: Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Shred
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Timeless GX
attacks.text: Take another turn after this one. (Skip the between-turns step.) (You can’t use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Spatial Control
attacks.text: Move any number of Energy from your Benched Pokémon to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Hydro Pressure
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage times the amount of {W} Energy attached to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Zero Vanish GX
attacks.text: Shuffle all Energy from each of your opponent's Pokémon into their deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

338690214.name: Crushing Hammer
338690214.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

338690215.name: Escape Board
338690215.text: The Retreat Cost of the Pokémon this card is attached to is {C} less, and it can retreat even if it’s Asleep or Paralyzed.

338690216.name: Missing Clover
338690216.text:
You may play 4 Missing Clover cards at once.

• If you played 1 card, look at the top card of your deck.
• If you played 4 cards, take a Prize card. (This effect works one time for 4 cards.)

338690217.name: Peeking Red Card
338690217.text: Your opponent reveals their hand. You may have your opponent count the cards in their hand, shuffle those cards into their deck, then draw that many cards.

338690218.name: Unit Energy {G}{R}{W}
338690218.text:
This card provides {C} Energy. 

While this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides {G}, {R}, and {W} Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time.

338690219.name: Unit Energy {L}{P}{M}
338690219.text:
This card provides {C} Energy. 

While this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides {L}, {P}, and {M} Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time.

abilities.name: Psychic Transfer
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a {P} Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Lunar Fall GX
attacks.text: Knock Out 1 of your opponent's Basic Pokémon that isn't a Pokémon-GX. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Moongeist Beam
attacks.text: The Defending Pokémon can’t be healed during your opponent's next turn.

abilities.name: Ultra Road
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Sol Burst GX
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 5 Energy cards and attach them to your Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 GX attack in a game.)

attacks.name: Sunsteel Strike
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

338746369.name: Sun & Moon—Ultra Prism
338746369.description: Pass through the Ultra Wormhole into a bizarre new Pokémon world, where familiar sights become strange and new powers are unlocked! Watch Necrozma’s power grow, and marvel as brand-new {*} cards reveal their astounding effects on play. Meet Dialga-GX and Palkia-GX, and encounter bizarre Ultra Beasts and wild new forms of Alola’s Legendary Pokémon. Explore a new dimension in the Pokémon TCG: Sun & Moon—Ultra Prism expansion!

338746370.name: Sun & Moon—Ultra Prism
338746370.description: Pass through the Ultra Wormhole into a bizarre new Pokémon world, where familiar sights become strange and new powers are unlocked! Watch Necrozma’s power grow, and marvel as brand-new {*} cards reveal their astounding effects on play. Meet Dialga-GX and Palkia-GX, and encounter bizarre Ultra Beasts and wild new forms of Alola’s Legendary Pokémon. Explore a new dimension in the Pokémon TCG: Sun & Moon—Ultra Prism expansion!

338746371.name: Sun & Moon—Ultra Prism Evolution Pack
338746371.description: A 23-card Sun & Moon—Ultra Prism Evolution pack, including 1 of 4 unique foil promo cards.

SM5ImperialCommandBundle.name: Imperial Command
SM5ImperialCommandBundle.description: The royal Empoleon is ready to lead Abomasnow and a team of Water types into battle! Together, they can overwhelm and freeze out foes with perfect timing. Unlock the power of ice, wind, and wave with the Imperial Command theme deck!

SM5ImperialCommandPCD.name: Imperial Command
SM5ImperialCommandPCD.description: The royal Empoleon is ready to lead Abomasnow and a team of Water types into battle! Together, they can overwhelm and freeze out foes with perfect timing. Unlock the power of ice, wind, and wave with the Imperial Command theme deck!

SM5MachStrikeBundle.name: Mach Strike
SM5MachStrikeBundle.description: A Dragon-type Pokémon knows that how you begin a battle determines how you end it—so call on Garchomp and Lucario, and go for the big attack with powerful hits at top speed! The Mach Strike theme deck pulls no punches!

SM5MachStrikePCD.name: Mach Strike
SM5MachStrikePCD.description: A Dragon-type Pokémon knows that how you begin a battle determines how you end it—so call on Garchomp and Lucario, and go for the big attack with powerful hits at top speed! The Mach Strike theme deck pulls no punches!

Sp18DawnWingsNecrozmaGXBundle.name: Wings of Dawn Deck
Sp18DawnWingsNecrozmaGXBundle.description: The star Pokémon-GX, plus Lunala, Bewear, Rayquaza, and Oranguru—prepare for a ferocious battle with strong Trainer support and big hits!

Sp18DuskManeNecrozmaGXBundle.name: Roar of Dusk Deck
Sp18DuskManeNecrozmaGXBundle.description: The star Pokémon-GX, plus Magnezone, Bewear, Registeel, Heatran, and great Trainer cards! Get ready for some heavy metal action with this one!
